For humans, CoVs have traditionally been considered non-lethal pathogens, mainly causing about 15% of common STDs.
However, in this century, we have two very deadly CoVs, SARS CoV and MERS-CoV, that caused epidemics in China in 2003 and Saudi Arabia in 2012 respectively and soon this terrible disease spread to many other countries with its death rate.
So the current COVID-19 is the third outbreak of CoV in recorded human history.
