Most are based on isopropyl alcohol or ethanol mixed in a concentrator, such as carbomer (a polysaccharide polysaccharide compound) in a jelly-like substance or a liquid such as glycerin foamed to a liquid or to ease use and reduce the drying effect of alcohol.
